related_items.title: Grim reminder in Ankara This super-bomb, placed before a statue depicting a peasant of the Turkish National Revolution in 1919-22, is regarded as a token to the people of the Turkish capital of what modern warfare would mean. This grim display was seen at Ankara less than two weeks ago. On Oct. 28, as Italian troops pushed across the Albanian border into Greece, it took on an even grimmer aspect. Turkey regards Greece as her friend and has said that she would consider an invasion of Greece a threat to the Dardanelles.
